description:
What if the secret to fixing back pain, avoiding dementia, and living longer is…your feet? Dr. Courtney Conley breaks down why your feet shoes are failing you.

Dr Courtney Conley is a physician specialising in feet. She is the founder of ‘Gait Happens’ and ‘Total Health Solutions’, where she aims to educate people about the importance of the human foot to overall health.

She explains: 
▫️How foot pain leads to emotional distress, depression, and inactivity
▫️How 500 extra steps a day can cut heart attack risk by 7%
▫️Why 4,000 steps a day can slash dementia risk by 50%
▫️How Courtney’s overcame addiction and used movement to save her life
▫️Why children’s shoes are sabotaging their future health

00:00 Intro  
02:20 Why Care About Feet  
05:54 The Most Common Foot Injuries  
07:36 What People Get Wrong About Foot Pain  
11:36 The Link Between Walking, Longevity, and Depression  
19:08 What Shoes Should I Wear to Help My Foot Strength?  
25:42 Our Feet vs. Tribe Feet  
27:56 Insoles Help Initially but Not Long Term  
30:45 1 in 3 People Will Develop Foot Pain  
31:24 Pain in the Heel (Plantar Fasciitis)  
33:51 Bigger Problems from Foot Issues  
35:21 Problems with Wearing Heels  
37:42 Characteristics of Good Shoes  
39:41 Super-Cushioned Running Shoes: Good or Bad?  
43:46 The Shocking Link Between Movement and Dementia  
45:03 The Rise of Run Clubs  
47:36 The Foot Gym  
48:13 Bunion Diagnoses  
57:00 Ads  
59:03 Importance of Strong Feet at the Gym  
1:06:05 What Is a Running Gait?  
1:09:49 Are We Supposed to Be Barefoot?  
1:17:29 Ads  
1:19:30 Should We Wear Socks?  
1:21:34 Viewer Comments  
1:23:34 What Happens After Ankle Injuries Heal  
1:26:45 What You'll Most Likely Regret in 10 Years

This represents everything wrong with "Experts" today. They focus on a thing in their career and then their ability to make money becomes the driving force behind making every single thing possible tied to their work to prop it up and give them new ways to promote their career..

Nothing undermines what you say like making a claim so absurd that it should cause everyone to question everything else you say.

P.S. All actual recent medical studies show that dementia effects walking, not the other way around and no, your hips and spine also do not cause dementia. Almost all forms of dementia is caused by either the shrinking of blood vessels in the brain or the clumping of different types of protein in the brain. Medical SCIENCE...done with actual scientific studies.

comments.text: I’m desperate for her help.  Bunions since I was 8, told it’s got to be genetic but nobody in my family has them. The surgeon admitted to removing pins too soon, but nothing to be done. Podiatrist after podiatrist saying there’s nothing to be done until I cannot walk… well over compensation lead to chiropractic scans showing a reversal of my cervical spine and DDD. I genuinely would love to seek her for help because I’ve given up on anyone I’ve met with, but am a single mom to two little girls who I plan to keep up with, or try…
